title: Sinkers .. Dumplings
ingredients: ["2 eggs", "3 cup milk", "7 cup all purpose flour", "1/2 tsp salt and pepper"]
directions: ["what are sinkers?", "idk.. my family been making them for a long time.", "it is basically a dumpling .only heavier.", "it is called a sinker for 2 reasons.", "1: they sink to the bottom of the pot when cooking and 2 they are heavy and sink to the bottom of your belly.", ":) they have no actual flavor.", "they are a great filler.", "the gravy is what gives them their awesomness.", "They also are great in soups.", "With mushroom gravy, pan gravy, white gravy, peppered gravy, sausage gravy, well any kind of gravy really!", ":)", "start boiling salted water in a large pot.", "only fill pot about halfway.", "the sinkers will raise the water.", "grab a big bowl.", "put the eggs n milk in bowl and whisk.", "pour in 2 cups.of flour and stir with a strong handled spoon.", "add 2 more cups of flour and stir again.", "add 1 cup flour and keep stirring.", "(warning.. your arm will get tired.", "and when you can not stir anymore and the flour doesn't seem to mix in, ditch the spoon and work with you're hands to knead the flour in)", "keep adding in flour 1/2 cup at a time.", "and keep mixing and kneading with hands until it is no longer sticky and you ran out of flour.", "(this will take some practice, its easy for me cuz I've been doing it for years.", "I know by feel, no matter they still are good)", "drop dough into boiling water by heaping tablespoon.", "(they will SINK to the bottom of the pot.)", "boil for about 20 minutes.", "after about 5 minutes give them a quick stir.. you will start to see the sinkers float after a while.", "once they are all floating cook for 10 more minutes..", "remove from water and transfer to a bowl to drain.", "to serve place a couple on a plate with your favorite meal and smother them with gravy.", "or put into a soup.", "I have mine with beef with mushroom gravy.. see recipe I have posted.", "it is awesome together..", "serves about 5-8 depending on what your doing with them"]

title: Cherry Pie With Almond Crumb Topping
ingredients: ["FOR THE PIE:", "1 whole Dough Recipe For Single Crust Pie, Your Favorite Or Prepared", "4 cups Cherries, Pitted. If Using Frozen, Thaw And Drain", "4 Tablespoons Cornstarch", "1/2 cups Sugar (can Adjust Based On Cherry Sweetness)", "1 Tablespoon Lemon Juice", "1/8 teaspoons Salt", "1 teaspoon Almond Extract", "1 Tablespoon Flour, For Sprinkling Onto Crust", "_____", "FOR THE TOPPING:", "1/2 cups Flour", "1/2 cups Sugar (white Or Brown, See Text)", "1/3 cups Oats, Old Fashioned", "1 cup Almonds, Sliced", "6 Tablespoons Butter, Melted", "1/2 teaspoons Almond Extract", "1/4 teaspoons Cinnamon (can Add More If You Want)", "1 pinch Salt"]
directions: ["For the crumb topping, I just winged it, adding equal parts of flour and sugar, some oats, lots of almonds and butter, a dash of cinnamon and salt and a bit of almond extract. I used about 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon, and I think it could have been even stronger. I was light handed with the cinnamon because I didn't want to overpower the almond extract (or clash with it). If you want it a little stronger, I leave that decision to your taste buds.", "I also used regular sugar, because I didn't want the crumbs to be too heavy and sweet, and it turned out great. However, it would probably be just as great with light brown sugar, so feel free to use that if you want a slightly stronger and sweeter crumb! I added the almond slices whole, and used a fork to combine the crumbs, breaking up the almond slices as I mixed. The almond breakage wasn't uniform, so it gave a nice variation in texture and taste. Don't worry about getting to every last little almond slice.", "Directions:", "1. Preheat oven to 375F", "2. Make the pie filling: Combine cherries, cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice, salt, and almond extract gently in a bowl.", "3. Place bottom crust in pie plate, and spread 1 Tablespoon of flour on the bottom crust. This will help prevent the bottom crust from getting soggy.", "4. Spoon filling into the bottom crust.", "5. Make the topping: Combine the flour, sugar, oats, almonds, butter, extract, cinnamon and salt, and mix until moistened. If it seems a little dry for you, add an extra Tablespoon of butter.", "6. Sprinkle the crumbs onto the pie as uniformly as you can, giving the best coverage that you can. Gently pat the crumbs into place.", "7. Bake at 375 for 1 hour to 1 hour 10 minutes. I put an aluminum shield on the crust about halfway through and it was perfect.", "8. Let cool completely on rack.", "Effort-wise, this pie was on par with a double-crust pie. Making the crumb topping takes about as much time as rolling a second crust. I have to say, I really enjoyed the change in flavor and texture that the crumb topping gave to this pie. The filling was the perfect contrast to the crumbs in every way, and each bite had the taste of buttery crust, tart cherries, and sweet crunchy crumbs.", "All in all, as you wind down your summer baking, and the last few weeks of good fruit come in, consider making this. The fresh ripe cherries won't be around much longer, so make haste!"]

ingredients: ["4 ounces chocolate", "1/2 cup water boiling", "1 cup margarine or butter", "2 cups sugar", "4 large eggs separated", "1 teaspoon vanilla extract", "2 1/4 cups flour, all-purpose sifted, or 2/12 cups cake flour", "1 teaspoon baking soda", "1/2 teaspoon salt", "1 cup buttermilk"]
directions: ["Melt chocolate in boiling water.", "Cool.", "Cream buter and sugar until fluffy.", "Add yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each.", "Blend in vanilla and chocolate.", "Sift flour with soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.", "Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in beaten whites.", "Pour into three 9-inch layer pans, lined on bottoms with paper.", "Bake at 350F (180C) for 30 to 35 minutes.", "Cool Frost tops only."]

title: Chef Bob's Chocolate Oatmeal Cookies
ingredients: ["1 cup milk", "1 cup shortening", "8 tablespoons cocoa (heaping)", "4 cups sugar", "1 cup peanut butter", "2 teaspoons vanilla", "5 cups quick oats"]
directions: ["Bring milk, shortening, cocoa, and sugar to a boil for 2-3 minutes - melting the sugar.", "Add peanut butter and vanilla.", "Stir and add oats.", "Stir again then drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.", "Allow to cool and set."]
